     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>The end and purpose of this Booke.</head>
   <l>LAy downe thy lofty lookes,</l>
   <l>Thy rich and rufling ragges,</l>
   <l>Sith God nor godly brookes,</l>
   <l>That beggars make such bragges.</l>
   <l>This wretched state you know,</l>
   <l>Shall soone be laide full lowe.</l>
   <l>Death puls thee by the sleeue,</l>
   <l>And cals thee to account:</l>
   <l>Thou wo<gap reason="illegible" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>â€¢</desc>
      </gap>st a moneth to liue,</l>
   <l>To what it doth amount.</l>
   <l>But least it be a weeke.</l>
   <l>Prepare: be not to seeke.</l>
   <l>Examine by this squire,</l>
   <l>And see if all be square,</l>
   <l>To scape that lasting fire,</l>
   <l>Flie paines, nor cost, nor care.</l>
   <l>To helpe thy life to looke,</l>
   <l>Tis purpose of this Booke.</l>
</div>
